    ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA STATUS:
      ✅ Editor mounts with locked extensions  ✅ DOCX byte input renders  ✅ serialize() exposed via ref  ✅ PaneEventBus events emitted (Flow 1 + Flow 2 per compose-contracts; "compose:document-changed" speculative POML name replaced with the locked contract names)  ✅ npm build + orchestrator build pass  ⏭ Browser ui-tests deferred to Phase 6 task 060 (no Chrome integration available in autonomous wave)  ⏭ TASK-INDEX flip handled by main session

    ADR TENSIONS: None. (compose-contracts.ts cross-cast through `unknown`/`any` is documented as adhering to ADR-030 additive contract; compose-contracts is solution-local per Spike #2 §11.)

    HEARTBEAT IMPL: 3-min sliding via setInterval, gated on `document.visibilityState === 'visible'`, calls `POST /api/compose/document/{documentId}/heartbeat` (singular `document` per Spike #3 §8) via `authenticatedFetch`. Defensive: logs warning + swallows non-2xx (W7-052 wires the BFF side; 404 today is expected and tolerated).

    ADR-013 (refined) verified: editor does NOT inject IOpenAiClient/IPlaybookService/AI internals. Only AI surface from editor is `compose_selection_offer` on the conversation channel — ConversationPane is the dispatcher to `POST /api/compose/action/{consumerType}` (W3-024). Facade boundary intact.

    ADR-015 Tier 3 verified: `selectionText` flows through PaneEventBus payloads (subscribers strip when bridging to telemetry per logFlowEvent reference impl). Document content (HTML from mammoth import) is NEVER console.log'd; only mammoth's `messages` array (Tier 1 safe configuration metadata) is logged.

